#Text=Benguet
#Text=Benguet Province is in Luzon in the Philippines .
#Text=Benguet is home to the Ibaloy , Kankana-ey , and Kalanguya peoples .
#Text=Benguet became a full province in 1968 .
#Text=Cities and towns
#Text=Benguet is divided into 13 municipalities , mostly rural and sparsely populated , each having a central town .
#Text=Baguio is the only city , but is politically independent from Benguet , but is still part of Benguet geographically .
#Text=– Dubbed the " Summer Capital of the Philippines " and " City of Pines " for its cool climate and pine trees , it is the tourist hub and the commercial center or the province .

column1: #Text=–
#Text=Provincial capitals , with its draws like its strawberry farms and a village with painted houses reminiscent of the favelas of Rio de Janeiro
#Text=Other destinations
#Text=– The second highest mountain in the Philippines , and the highest in Luzon .
#Text=Geography
#Text=Benguet occupies over of land area , mostly mountainous terrain .
#Text=The capital is La Trinidad .
#Text=At above sea level , the province lies on top of the Cordillera Mountains containing Mount Pulag , the second highest mountain in the Philippines .
#Text=Amidst these mountain peaks is a wide plateau wherein the capital town , La Trinidad , is located .
#Text=The province is bounded on the south by Pangasinan and on the west by La Union and Ilocos Sur , Benguet serves as the gateway to the highland provinces of the Cordillera Region .
#Text=Climate
#Text=Benguet has a more temperate climate due to its altitude .
#Text=Daytime highs rarely reach , but the nighttime lows can reach below during the cool season , causing frost that can destroy vegetables .
#Text=People

#Text=In the sparsely populated Cordillera Region , Benguet stands out as having the highest population among the provinces with over 300 thousand and a population density of over 115 people per square km ( 300 people per square mile ) .
#Text=Migrants have joined the local tribes such as the Kankana-eys , Ibaloys and Kalanguyas to settle in this rich highland province .
#Text=Although the three tribes speak different languages and dialects , they share similar cultures and have common beliefs and rituals .
#Text=History
#Text=During the Spanish Era , Benguet was not a remote area for the Spaniards to explore .
#Text=The vastness and promising economic potential of the place lured the Spaniards to conduct a series of expeditions .
#Text=Series of attempts to pacify the " Igorots " but failed .
#Text=Finally in 1846 , commandante de Galvey established his Commandante at La Trinidad , Benguet ( named after his wife ) .
#Text=The first Kapitan of Benguet was Pulito of Kafagway , Now Baguio , a minor rancheria of about 20 houses .
#Text=The Americans came early in 1900 and established its government with H. Whitmarsh as the appointed governor of Benguet and Baguio City as the capital .
#Text=This was the first provincial government to be established in the Philippines and this happened a year prior to the inauguration of the civil government of the Philippines .

#Text=Their best administrators and teachers were fervent boosters and promoters : Worcester , Wright Forbes , Pack Barrows , Eckman and others who together with Filipinos committed to make the place a haven .
#Text=The mines near Baguio were developed and became productive .
#Text=Business in the city flourished with commercial centers put up .
#Text=Recreation facilities were installed .
#Text=The city was growing before the outbreak of the war .

#Text=Baguio was bombed December 8 , 1941 by the Japanese and they occupied it on December 27 of the same year , However , the war changed course and on September 3 , 1945 , General Yamashita surrendered to the Americans at the US Ambassador 's residence in Camp John Hay , after which , Baguio immediately set to the task of rehabilitation .
#Text=Talk
#Text=The major language is Ilocano , brought by lowland migrants who settled in the province , but there are also many indigenous languages , such as Kankana-ey , Ibaloi , and Kalanguya .
#Text=The people of the province can also converse in English , especially the younger populations .
#Text=Ilocano or Tagalog is much useful when communicating with locals .
#Text=Get in

#Text=The province of Benguet can be accessed through five national roads ; Kennon Road , Aspiras – Palispis Highway and Naguilian Road are the main routes coming from Manila , while the Benguet-Nueva Vizcaya Road and Halsema Highway offer entry to the Province of Nueva Vizcaya and to the rest of the Cordillera Region .
#Text=Benguet can also be reached by air through the Loakan airport in Baguio City , but is limited to general aviation and private aircraft .
#Text=Get around
#Text=One can get around the province by public transportation such as jeepney , bus , and passenger bus .
#Text=Taxis are limited around Baguio and La Trinidad , and the more ubiquitous tricycle replace them in the towns .

#Text=By road , the most important highway is the winding Halsema Highway ( Route 204 , officially the Baguio-Bontoc Road ) , which starts at La Trinidad and stretching north through the town of Bontoc in Mountain Province .
#Text=It is a critical lifeline between the mountain towns and Baguio , has the highest point in the Philippine highway network , at above sea level over the municipality of Atok .
#Text=Driving there is quite dangerous due to the numerous sharp curves , unguarded cliffs , and landslides during rainy season .
#Text=Halsema Highway is a toll road , and you must pay ₱20 at the toll barriers at each end of the highway .
#Text=If you have your own vehicle but are not familiar with the town you want to visit , people will be willing to help you with the directions .
#Text=See
#Text=Benguet Museum , Capitol , La Trinidad , 2601 Benguet .
#Text=M - F 9AM-5PM .
#Text=Provincial museum containing ethnographic materials relating to the indigenous people of Benguet .
#Text=Free .
#Text=Kabayan Branch Museum , Kabayan .
#Text=M - Sa 8AM-noon , 1-5PM. Kabayan Museum is established to protect and care the Kabayan Mummy Caves in the province .
#Text=Mummy Caves are one of the country 's national cultural treasures .
#Text=It is a burial caves that holds mummies sited in Kabayan especially in the Timbac Caves .
#Text=The building is placed in a lot donated by citizens who value the culture of the Ibaloi and the Kankanaey .
#Text=It is a one-story building and a basement builds in a 500-m² lot in 1989 .
#Text=Also kept here are ethnographical , ecological and geological collections including artifacts and other relics of the Kabayan Mummies .
#Text=Free .
#Text=Historical sites and land marks
#Text=Camp Utopia ( Sagubo , Kapangan ) :
#Text=This was the camp of the 66th Infantry Battalion during the Second World War .
#Text=It was also the site where the late Major Bado Dangwa and Major Dennis Molintas led the defense of the Igorotlandia .
#Text=Kaliwaga Cave ( Kaliwaga , Kapangan ) : The burial place of the British soldiers of fortune who came to Benguet during the 15th century .

#Text=Guerilla Saddle ( Km . 26 , Atok ) : Where the fiercest battle between the advancing Japanese Imperial Forces and the United States Armed Forces - 66th Infantry was fought to the advantage of the guerrilla resistance movement .
#Text=A lot of Japanese soldiers have fallen and perished on this spot .
#Text=Thus , Atok is known as the Vanguard of Freedom in Benguet .
#Text=Darew Ancient Ruins of Civilization ( Kapangan ) : Located at the top of the mountain west of Kapangan .
#Text=It commands a vantage view of the coastline to the west and fertile valley to the east .
#Text=For many years , the people lived in peace and prosperity .

#Text=From this area , they traded and intermarried , forged alliances and came to recognize as kin those who lived in more populous settlements of Tagudin , Agoo , Tubao , Ambanganan ( Pugo ) , Lingayen , Dagupan , Binalonan , Tayug , Safid ( San Manuel ) , Imogen , Ituy , Tinok and Ahin .
#Text=Hill WW II ( Mankayan ) : Site where the 66th Infantry Battalion and guerrillas fought to make their way to Besang Pass .
#Text=The capture of Hill WW II opened the right flank guard of the Japanese Imperial Garrison to bombardment and constant attack by Igorot freedom fighters .

#Text=Lamtang ( Puguis , La Trinidad ) : The escape route of then President Sergio Osmena and party who were escorted by a detachment of the 66th Infantry Battalion to Camp Valhalla , Kapangan then to San Gabriel , La Union during the World War II .
#Text=Klondykes Stone Walls ( Klondykes , Tuba ) : Remnant of the first American building used by the American engineers who constructed Kennon Road .
#Text=It is believed to have been built in 1902 and is still visible today .
#Text=Cariño Cave ( Eddet , Kabayan ) : The hiding place of Governor Ora Cariño and the place where he was captured by the Americans in 1900 .
#Text=Manenchen ( Manenchen , Kabayan ) : The site of the massacre of Eddet residents by the Japanese Imperial Army during the World War II .
#Text=Kennon Road ( Tuba ) : One of the legacies of the American Administration .
#Text=It was the first Benguet road to be constructed by the Americans in 1902 .

#Text=The completion of this road opened the entire Benguet Province to vehicular traffic and marked the entry of Americans , Europeans , Japanese , Chinese and lowlanders to the Province of Benguet .

#Text=It was referred as the Benguet Road until it was renamed Kennon Road by virtue of Executive Order No. 9 in 1922 , in honor of Col. Lyman W. Kennon , the American engineer who supervised and finished the construction of the road in 1905 .
#Text=Kabayan Pyramid ( Poblacion , Kabayan ) :
#Text=It is also called the " Kinepol ni Nabaloi . "
#Text=The burial tomb of Henry A. Kamora , the Grand Old Man of Kabayan which is located at the municipal compound .
#Text=Embosi :
#Text=It is the first known Ibaloi settlement .
#Text=The place is found at Gusaran , Kabayan .
